22 May 2015 WHO: At least 30 countries, mainly in Africa, would struggle against Ebola, WHO warns as it pours in more cash
http://mgafrica.com/article/2015-05-21-these-28-countries-would-struggle-with-major-health-outbreaks-who-warns-as-it-pours-in-more-cash/
[The World Health Organization reports that nations like Burundi, Sudan, Democratic Republic of the Congo, and Madagascar have health systems as dangerously weak as Ebola-hit Guinea, Liberia and Sierra Leone's.]

20 May 2015 World Bank: supports improved maternal and child health services in Guinea beyond Ebola outbreak
http://www.worldbank.org/en/news/press-release/2015/05/20/guinea-world-bank-supports-improved-maternal-and-child-health-services-beyond-ebola-outbreak
[The World Bank Group's Board of Executive Directors today [20 May 2015] approved USD 15.1 million for women and children to expand access to maternal and child health and nutrition services in Faranah and Labe, 2 of the poorest regions in Guinea.]

